# WHAT IT IS
#   In industrial automation, a **PLC (Programmable Logic
#   Controller)** is a real-time deterministic computer that
#   reads inputs from sensors (level switches, pressure
#   transducers, flow meters, current transformers,
#   photoelectric sensors, encoders) and writes outputs to
#   actuators (relays, contactors, solenoids, variable-speed
#   drives, hydraulic valves, servo motors) on a strict cycle
#   (typically 1 ms to 100 ms scan time).  Historically these
#   are vendor-locked devices programmed in IEC 61131-3
#   languages (Ladder Logic, Structured Text, Function Block
#   Diagram, Sequential Function Chart, Instruction List)
#   running on Siemens S7 / Allen-Bradley ControlLogix /
#   Schneider Modicon / Beckhoff TwinCAT / B&R X20 / Mitsubishi
#   MELSEC iQ-R / Omron CJ2 / Rockwell PLC-5 / GE 90-30 /
#   Honeywell Experion / Yokogawa Centum hardware.
#
#   `rplc` lets a Rust programmer write the same kind of
#   deterministic control logic in Rust, compile it to a
#   native binary that runs on any Linux SBC (Raspberry Pi /
#   BeagleBone / Up Squared / Mac Mini / industrial NUC), and
#   integrate it into a wider SCADA system via its built-in
#   **OPC UA server + client** (so HMIs from Inductive
#   Automation Ignition, AVEVA System Platform, Siemens WinCC,
#   Wonderware InTouch, Rockwell FactoryTalk View ME/SE,
#   Iconics GENESIS64, ICONICS Hyper-Historian, GE Cimplicity,
#   COPA-DATA zenon, B-Scada Status, OPC Router, Kepware
#   KEPServerEX, or any other OPC UA-speaking SCADA client can
#   connect natively).
#
#   The `rplc` binary itself is the operator-side CLI for
#   managing a fleet of rPLC programs:
#
#     ŌĆó Register / unregister rPLC programs as systemd units
#       with full task-affinity + CPU-pinning + priority
#       configuration
#     ŌĆó Start / stop / restart / status rPLC programs via
#       systemd
#     ŌĆó List all registered rPLC programs on the host
#     ŌĆó Query a running rPLC's per-task statistics (cycle
#       time, jitter, missed deadlines, worst-case execution
#       time)
#     ŌĆó Reset per-task statistics
#     ŌĆó Query a running rPLC's tag/IO info
#     ŌĆó Test a rPLC program (run-once mode without systemd)
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from src/cli.rs clap-derive
#                       `Args` struct + `Command` enum +
#                       `PlcParams` / `PlcRegisterParams` /
#                       `ListParams` arg structs; extracted via
#                       raw.githubusercontent.com fetch of
#                       src/cli.rs)
#
#   rplc [GLOBAL OPTIONS] <COMMAND> [ARGS...]
#
#   Global options:
#     -h, --help                     Show help
#     -V, --version                  Print version
#     --color <MODE>                 Color override
#                                    [values: always, never]
#
#   Commands:
#     list [OPTIONS]                 List PLCs
#     test <PLC>                     Test PLC (run-once mode)
#     info <PLC>                     Print PLC info (registered
#                                    tags, IO, OPC-UA endpoints)
#     stat <PLC>                     Print per-task statistics
#                                    (cycle time, jitter, worst-
#                                    case execution time, missed
#                                    deadlines)
#     reset <PLC>                    Reset per-task statistics
#     register <PLC_FILE_PATH> [OPTIONS]
#                                    Register a rPLC binary as a
#                                    systemd unit
#         -a <NAME=CPU,PRIORITY>     Thread affinity (repeatable)
#         -e, --eapi <CONN>          EVA ICS bus connection:
#                                    path[,timeout=Xs]
#                                       [,buf_size=X]
#                                       [,queue_size=X]
#                                       [,buf_ttl=Xms]
#         --var <NAME=VALUE>         Custom environment variable
#                                    (repeatable)
#         --force                    Overwrite existing
#                                    registration
#         -s, --start                Start PLC after registration
#     unregister <PLC>               Unregister PLC binary from
#                                    systemd (stops if running)
#     start <PLC>                    Start PLC with systemd
#     stop <PLC>                     Stop PLC with systemd
#     restart <PLC>                  Restart PLC with systemd
#     status <PLC>                   Print PLC systemd status
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   `eva-ics/rplc` declares a **direct** dependency on
#   `rplc_opcua = { version = "0.12.1", optional = true }` in its
#   `Cargo.toml`, gated behind the `opcua` feature
#   (`opcua = ["rplc_opcua", "ttl_cache"]`).  `rplc_opcua` is **a
#   maintained Altertech fork of the canonical Rust OPC UA
#   library** at `locka99/opcua` (the canonical Rust OPC UA
#   implementation by Adam Lock, 570+ Ōśģ on GitHub, the de-facto
#   Rust OPC UA SDK on crates.io with 66,130+ all-time downloads).
#
#   `locka99/opcua` (crate `opcua`; current version 0.12.0, with
#   the `rplc_opcua` fork at 0.12.4) is **THE canonical Rust
#   implementation of OPC UA** ŌĆö the IEC 62541 standard for
#   industrial automation system interoperability that has, since
#   ~2010, displaced OPC Classic (DA / HDA / A&E / DCOM-based) as
#   the universal SCADA-to-controller communication protocol.
#   OPC UA implementations exist in the IEC 62541 reference C/C++
#   stack (open62541), the official OPC Foundation .NET reference
#   stack, the Eclipse Milo Java reference stack, the canonical
#   Python implementation at FreeOpcUa/python-opcua-asyncio, the
#   canonical Go implementation at gopcua/opcua, the canonical
#   TypeScript implementation at node-opcua/node-opcua, and this
#   canonical Rust implementation at locka99/opcua (plus the
#   newer maintained FreeOpcUa/async-opcua at 123+ Ōśģ which is the
#   tokio-async-rewrite of locka99/opcua).
#
#   `opcua` (locka99) exposes:
#
#     ŌĆó Typed `Server::new(config)` /
#       `Server::add_endpoint(endpoint)` /
#       `Server::add_address_space(node_manager)` /
#       `Server::start()` typed server lifecycle API
#     ŌĆó Typed `Client::new(config)` /
#       `client.connect_to_endpoint(endpoint, session_endpoint)`
#       /  `client.new_session_from_endpoint(endpoint, identity_token)`
#       /  `session.read(nodes_to_read, timestamps_to_return, max_age)`
#       /  `session.write(nodes_to_write)` /
#       `session.browse(nodes_to_browse)` /
#       `session.create_subscription(...)` /
#       `session.create_monitored_items(...)` /
#       `session.call(method_call)` /
#       `session.call_one(method_call)` /
#       `session.history_read(...)` /
#       `session.history_update(...)` typed client API
#     ŌĆó Typed OPC UA address-space model ŌĆö every `BaseObjectType`
#       /  `BaseVariableType` /  `BaseDataVariableType` /
#       `PropertyType` /  `BaseEventType` /  `ServerType` /
#       `FolderType` /  `MethodType` typed object node, every
#       `Boolean` /  `SByte` /  `Byte` /  `Int16` /  `UInt16` /
#       `Int32` /  `UInt32` /  `Int64` /  `UInt64` /  `Float` /
#       `Double` /  `String` /  `DateTime` /  `Guid` /
#       `ByteString` /  `XmlElement` /  `NodeId` /  `ExpandedNodeId`
#       /  `StatusCode` /  `QualifiedName` /  `LocalizedText` /
#       `ExtensionObject` /  `DataValue` /  `Variant`
#       discriminated-union built-in OPC UA scalar type
#     ŌĆó Typed `MessageSecurityMode::None` /
#       `Sign` /  `SignAndEncrypt` security-mode enum
#     ŌĆó Typed `SecurityPolicy::None` /
#       `Basic128Rsa15` /  `Basic256` /  `Basic256Sha256` /
#       `Aes128Sha256RsaOaep` /  `Aes256Sha256RsaPss` security-
#       policy URI enum
#     ŌĆó Typed `IdentityToken::Anonymous` /
#       `UserName(username, password)` /
#       `X509(cert, key_path)` typed authentication-token
#       discriminated union
#     ŌĆó Typed `MonitoringMode::Disabled` /  `Sampling` /
#       `Reporting` enum
#     ŌĆó Typed `BrowseDirection::Forward` /  `Inverse` /  `Both`
#       enum + typed `ReferenceTypeId::HasComponent` /
#       `HasProperty` /  `HasSubtype` /  `HasTypeDefinition` /
#       `Organizes` /  `HasModellingRule` /  `HasNotifier` /
#       `HasEventSource` /  `HasCondition` /  `HasEffect` /
#       `GeneratesEvent` /  `AlwaysGeneratesEvent` /
#       `HasEncoding` /  `HasDescription` /  `HierarchicalReferences`
#       /  `NonHierarchicalReferences`
